  "prompt": "Can you use a Visa gift card on Amazon?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use a Visa gift card on Amazon. Here's how:\n\n1.  **Redeem the Gift Card to Your Amazon Account:**\n    *   Go to \"Your Account\" on Amazon.\n    *   Click on \"Gift Cards.\"\n    *   Click \"Redeem a Gift Card\"\n    *   Enter the gift card number and PIN.\n    *   The balance will be added to your Amazon account.\n\n2.  **Use the Balance at Checkout:**\n    *   During the checkout process, you can apply your Amazon gift card balance as payment.\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Make sure the gift card has enough balance to cover the order, including shipping and taxes.** You can also combine it with another payment method, like a credit or debit card.\n*   **Visa gift cards cannot be reloaded.** Once the balance is used, the card is no longer valid.\n*   **Some Visa gift cards may require activation.** If you have trouble using it, double-check that it has been activated.\n*   **Be careful of scams.** Never provide your gift card number or PIN to someone you don't trust. Only redeem the gift card directly on the Amazon website or app.\n\nBy redeeming the Visa gift card to your Amazon account, you effectively convert it into Amazon credit, which can then be used for purchases on the site.\n",
